# Feature-Sliced Design Rules

The application follows **Feature-Sliced Design (FSD)**.

Layers

app
pages
widgets
features
entities
shared

---

# Shared

shared contains reusable utilities and UI components.

shared/ui contains atomic UI components.

shared/lib contains utilities.

shared/api contains base API clients.

---

# Entities

Entities represent domain models.

Example:

entities/user
entities/product

Entities may contain:

model
api
ui

---

# Features

Features represent user actions.

Examples:

login
add-to-cart
comment

Features may contain:

ui
model
api
tests

---

# Widgets

Widgets compose UI blocks using features and entities.

Example:

header
sidebar
product-list

---

# Pages

Pages compose widgets only.

Pages must not contain business logic.
